description: Costing per elevator. Traction elevator components in the machine room contain a controller, machine, motor generator, governor, and tail sheave.
name: Traction Elevator Machine room components. Applies to Seismic Zone 2 and elevators designed according to the ASME A17.1-2007 Standard or similar.
name_short: Traction Elevator Machine room components. Seismic Zone 2
author: HBRG

description: Costing per elevator. Cab and Counterweight components are changing in levels from ground to roof and have an equal probability of being on any floor.
name: Traction Elevator Cab and Counterweight Components. Applies to Seismic Zone 2 and elevators designed according to the ASME A17.1-2007 Standard or similar.
name_short: Traction Elevator Cab and Counterweight Components. Seismic Zone 2
author: HBRG

description: Costing per elevator. Guide rail is the only component that is continuous from ground to roof. This represents a set of guide rails per elevator system (typically 4 rails per elevator). Under normal circumstances, guide rails simply define the elevator paths that elevators ride along and are assumed to be spared from the loads and forces imposed on the elevator cars.
name: Traction Elevator Guide Rails. Applies to Seismic Zone 2 and elevators designed according to the ASME A17.1-2007 Standard or similar.
name_short: Traction Elevator Guide Rails. Seismic Zone 2
author: HBRG

description: Costing per elevator. Rail brackets attach guiderails to the hoistway walls and are typically located at each floor. A bracket is required at top or hoistway and an intermediate bracket may be required for excessive floor-to-floor heights
name: Traction Elevator Guide Rail Brackets. Applies to Seismic Zone 2 and elevators designed according to the ASME A17.1-2007 Standard or similar.
name_short: Traction Elevator Guide Rail Brackets. Seismic Zone 2
